<en-note><div>Apache-MySQL-PHP Installation</div><div><span style="font: 21.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font: 21.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">Apache 2.4 Server</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;" color="#929292"># To see the Apache version on your Mac OS X:</font></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">=&gt;<font color="#ff2600"> </font></span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Menlo;"><font color="#ff2600">sudo</font> <font color="#941100">/usr/sbin/httpd -V</font></span></font></div><div><font color="#929292"># To check if the Apacher Server is running:</font></div><div>=&gt; <font color="#ff2600">sudo</font><b> apachect</b>l   <font color="#929292"># If it returns nothing means it is NOT running</font></div><div><font color="#929292"># To start the Server:</font></div><div><span style="font: 18.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; <font color="#ff2600">sudo</font> </span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><b>apachectl</b></span><span style="font: 18.0px Helvetica;"> <font color="#009193">start</font></span></div><div><span style="font: 18.0px Helvetica;"><font color="#929292"># To check the HTTPD main config file syntax:</font></span></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">=&gt;<font style="font-weight: normal;" color="#ff2600"> sudo </font><b>apachectl</b></span><span style="font: 18.0px Helvetica;"> <font color="#0433ff">configtest</font></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">The main configuration file is </font></span><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"> “</span><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;"><font color="#941100">/etc/apache2</font>/</span><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(4, 51, 255); font-weight: bold;">httpd.conf</span><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">”</span></div><div>The Apache Server will run under:</div><div><b>User </b><font color="#008f00">_www</font></div><div><b>Group</b> <font color="#009193">_www</font></div><div><span style="font: 18.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font: 18.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">System Level Web Root</span><span style="font: 18.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold;"> :</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;"> </span></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><a style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(146, 146, 146);" href="http://localhost">http://localhost</a><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;"> </span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">and documents are located</span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">in “</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;"><font color="#941100">/Library/WebServer/Documents/</font>&quot;</span></font></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font: 18.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">User Level Root</span></div><div><br/></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">The physical location <font color="#941100">“</font></span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;"><font color="#941100">~/Sites</font></span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">” (</span><span style="font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: italic;"><font color="#941100">/Users/khasanov/</font></span><span style="font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;"><font color="#941100">Sites</font></span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">).</span></font></div><div><ol start="1"><li><span style="font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;">You need to create this folder first.</span><br/></li></ol></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span>    <span>    </span></span>=&gt; <b>mkdir</b><font color="#941100"> /Users/khasanov/Sites</font></font></span></div><div><ol start="2"><li><span style="font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 18px;">Then create a config file under “<font color="#941100">/etc/apache2/users</font>” for this user:</span><br/></li></ol></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-weight: normal;">    <span>    </span></span>=&gt; <font style="font-weight: normal;" color="#ff2600">sudo</font><b> vim</b><font color="#941100"> /etc/apache2/users/</font><font color="#0433ff">khasanov.conf</font> and add the content:</font></span></div><div><span style="font: 17.0px Courier;"><span>    </span><font color="#9437ff">&lt;Directory</font> &quot;<font color="#941100">/Users/khasanov/Sites/</font>&quot;&gt;</span></div><div><span style="font: 17.0px Courier;"><span>    <span>    </span></span><font color="#ff40ff">AllowOverride</font> <font color="#4f8f00">All</font></span></div><div><span style="font: 17.0px Courier;"><span>       <font color="#ff40ff"> </font></span><font color="#ff40ff">Options</font> Indexes MultiViews FollowSymLinks</span></div><div><span style="font: 17.0px Courier;"><span>    <span>    </span></span><font color="#ff40ff">Require</font> <font color="#4f8f00">all granted</font></span></div><div><span style="font: 17.0px Courier;"><span>    </span><font color="#9437ff">&lt;/Directory&gt;</font></span></div><div><span style="font: 17.0px Courier;"><font color="#9437ff"><br/></font></span></div><div><ol start="3"><li><span style="font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;">Set the permission to 644:</span><br/></li></ol></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><span>    <span>    </span></span>=&gt; sudo </span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">chmo</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">d 644<font color="#941100"> </font></span><span style="font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: italic;"><font color="#941100">/ec/apache2/users/</font></span><span style="font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;"><font color="#0433ff">khasanov.conf</font></span></font></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font: 19.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Loading Modules in the “httpd.conf”</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">Edit the “/etc/apache2/httpd.conf” and make sure that the following module is loaded:</font></span></div><div><font face="Helvetica"><font color="#0096ff">LoadModule</font> <font color="#941100">userdir_module libexec/apache2/</font><font color="#0096ff">mod_userdir.so</font></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br/></font></div><div><font face="Helvetica"># Let to read what is in the “httpd-userdir.conf”:</font><br/></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Courier; font-weight: bold;">Include</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Courier;"> <font color="#941100">/private/etc/apache2/extra/</font></span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Courier; font-weight: bold;">httpd-userdir.conf</span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br/></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;" color="#929292"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">#  Edit the &quot;</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Courier;">/etc/apache2/extra/httpd-userdir.conf”file add the following:</span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;" color="#929292"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Courier;"># ( if its not present )</span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Courier; font-weight: bold;">Include</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Courier;"> /private/etc/apache2/users/</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Courier; font-weight: bold;">*.conf</span></font></div><div><span style="font-family: Courier;"><font color="#9437ff">&lt;IfModule</font> <font color="#0096ff">bonjour_module</font>&gt;</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Courier;">       <b>RegisterUserSite</b> customized-users</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Courier;"><font color="#9437ff">&lt;/IfModule&gt;</font></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Courier; font-weight: bold;"><br/></span></font></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;"><font style="font-size: 24px;">Test the Configuration:</font></span></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br/></font></span></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">=&gt; sudo apachectl restart</font></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">Visit <font color="#797979">http:</font></span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;"><font color="#797979">//localhost/~khasanov/</font></span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;"><br/></span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><en-media hash="f77459eb7023de93621c800993f2dff7" type="image/tiff"/></font></div><div><span style="font: 21.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">PHP Test</span></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br/></font></span></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;"># The PHP is installed by default and we have already loaded the PHP module in</font></span></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;"># the “http.conf” file. </font></span></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;"># Now we are going to write a PHP test file and put it under the “~/Sites” folder:</font></span></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">=&gt;<b> vim</b><font color="#941100"> /Users/khasanov/Sites/</font><font color="#008f00">testphp.php</font></font></span></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;"><font color="#9437ff">&lt;?php</font> <font color="#0433ff">phpinfo();</font> <font color="#9437ff">?&gt;</font></font></span></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br/></font></span></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">Visit “<a href="http://localhost/~khasanov/testphp.php">http://localhost/~khasanov/testphp.php</a>” and you should see the PHP Info page.</font></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font: 21.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">MySQL Installation and Setup</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">MySQL is not the part of the OS X 10.11, so you need to download and install it.</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Get it from the MySQL site and use the Mac OS X 10.10 (x86, 64-bit), DMG Archive</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">version ( which works on 10.11).</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Important ! You must write down a given temporary password which you need later.</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-style: italic; text-decoration: underline;">To start the MySQL Server:</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; </span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; color: #ff2600;">sudo</span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; font-weight: bold;">launchctl load -F</span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier;">  </span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; font-style: italic;">/Library/LaunchDaemons/</span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">com.oracle.oss.mysql.mysqld.plist</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-style: italic; text-decoration: underline;">To stop the MySQL Server:</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; </span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; color: #ff2600;">sudo</span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; font-weight: bold;">launchctl unload -F </span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier;"> </span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; font-style: italic;">/Library/LaunchDaemons/</span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">com.oracle.oss.mysql.mysqld.plist</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-style: italic; text-decoration: underline;">To change the default ( temporary) password:</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; </span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; font-style: italic;">/usr/local/mysql/bin/</span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; font-weight: bold;">mysqladmin</span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier;"> -u </span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; color: #ff2600;">root</span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier;"> -p'</span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; color: #ff40ff;">temppassword</span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier;">' </span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; font-weight: bold;">password</span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier;"> '</span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; color: #0433ff;">newpassword</span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier;">'</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-style: italic; text-decoration: underline;">To login as a root</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; </span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; font-style: italic;">/usr/local/</span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; font-weight: bold;">mysql</span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier;"> -v -u </span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; color: #ff2600;">root</span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier;"> -p</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-style: italic; text-decoration: underline;">To fix the 2002 MySQL Socket error:</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; </span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier;">sudo mkdir /var/mysql</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; </span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier;">sudo ln -s /tmp/mysql.sock /var/mysql/mysql.sock</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font: 22.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">phpMyAdmin Installation and Configuration</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Download the phpMyAdmin and extract it and then </span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; copy the phpMyAdmin </span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">root folder</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;"> to “</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">phpmyadmin&quot;</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">=&gt; sudo cp -r </span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">phpmyadmin</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">  </span><span style="font: 14.0px Menlo; color: #cccccc;">/Library/WebServer/Documents/</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;"> ( i.e.System document root ). </span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;"> Note: If you have installed the MySQL Server your way, you might still get </span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; color: #ff2600;">Error: 2002 - No such file or</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; color: #ff2600;">  directory</span></div><div><span style="font: 22.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Creating the WordPress Database</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">Using the phpMyAdmin</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">•</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Login the phpMyAdmin  as a root at </span><a style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;" href="http://localhost/phpmyadmin">http://localhost/phpmyadmin</a></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">•</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Create the WordPress as shown below</span></div><div><en-media hash="f2a6a964840996edbb0f0ddc9697af49" type="image/png"/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">•</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Create the WP user (Leave all options under Global privileges at their defaults):</span></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Courier;">  </span></div><div><en-media hash="be9a439b1947e3582efc125d07ab02a0" type="image/png"/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">•</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Give  the WP User privilege to use the “reinforces_db”:</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;"> </span></div><div><en-media hash="1d8e8fdb31c092244068c5a12c91af26" type="image/png"/></div><div><span style="font: 14.0px Courier;"> Click </span><span style="font: 14.0px Courier; font-weight: bold;">Go</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">•</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Edit the privileges and click on </span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">Check all </span></div><div><br/></div><div><en-media hash="8bb74be8d88961ce5993dc0d68e85473" type="image/png"/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Using the Command Line:</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">$ </span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">mysql</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;"> -u</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; color: #ff2600;"> root</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;"> -p</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-style: italic;">mysql&gt;</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;"> </span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; color: #0433ff;">CREATE DATABASE</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-weight: bold;"> kfhweb_db</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">;</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-style: italic;">mysql&gt;</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;"> </span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; color: #0433ff;">GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;"> kfhweb_db.* </span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; color: #0433ff;">TO</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;"> “WP_user”@“localhost” </span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; color: #0433ff;">IDENTIFIED BY</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;"> “hassan3”;</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-style: italic;">mysql&gt;</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;"> </span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; color: #0433ff;">FLUSH PRIVILEGES</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">;</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; font-style: italic;">mysql&gt;</span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;"> </span><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica; color: #0433ff;">EXIT </span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Installing the WordPress</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Step 1 : Create a folder called “/Users/khasanov/Sites/karshi.ca” and extract the latest.tar.gz to the folder.</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Step 2: Change the ownership of the folder to “_www” :</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">            =&gt; sudo chown -R _www </span><a style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;" href="http://karshi.ca">karshi.ca</a></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Step 3: Copy the  “wp-config-sample.php” —&gt; “wp-config.php”</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">             =&gt; sudo cp wp-config-sample.php wp-config.php</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Step 4: Modify the “wp-config.php” : Set “DB_NAME” , “DB_USER” and “DB_PASSWORD”</span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">Step 5: Run </span><a style="font: 14.0px Courier;" href="http://localhost/~khasanov/karshi.ca/wp-admin/install.php">http://localhost/~khasanov/karshi.ca/wp-admin/install.php</a></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">            </span></div><div><en-media hash="23109cc6582873d8e0eac0bac93f27fe" type="image/png"/></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;"> </span></div><div><span style="font: 12.0px Helvetica;">  </span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>
